{"question_id": "syn-pdfQA/03_Raw_Question_Answer_Data/research articles/2510.22211v1_rawQA.json#9", "question": "Is there evidence that Ansky is a featureless TDE with a longer evolution timescale and lower luminosity than typical TDEs, likely resulting from the tidal disruption of a post-main-sequence star by a supermassive black hole?", "answers": ["Yes"], "prediction": "yes", "raw_answer": "Yes, there is evidence that Ansky is a featureless TDE with a longer evolution timescale and lower luminosity than typical TDEs, likely resulting from the tidal disruption of a post-main-sequence star by a supermassive black hole. This conclusion is supported by its persistent absence of broad emission lines, slower rise and decline timescales, lower blackbody luminosity (~10^43 erg s^-1), and the proposed tidal disruption scenario consistent with its observed properties.\n\n引用页码与关键关系: 11, 8; keyword::featureless_tde --[keyword_hit]--> 2510_22211v1_page11_text_5, keyword::post_ms_star --[keyword_hit]--> 2510_22211v1_page8_text_3", "source_hint": "2510.22211v1.pdf", "doc_name": "2510.22211v1.pdf", "category": "syn", "dataset": "03_Raw_Question_Answer_Data", "question_type": "unknown", "evidence_pages": [], "pages": [2, 6, 8, 9, 11, 12], "node_ids": ["2510_22211v1_page11_text_5", "2510_22211v1_page11_text_8", "2510_22211v1_page8_text_11", "2510_22211v1_page12_text_0", "2510_22211v1_page6_text_4", "2510_22211v1_page6_figure_0", "2510_22211v1_page8_figure_0", "2510_22211v1_page11_figure_0", "2510_22211v1_page8_text_0", "2510_22211v1_page8_text_1", "2510_22211v1_page8_text_2", "2510_22211v1_page8_text_3", "2510_22211v1_page8_text_4", "2510_22211v1_page8_text_5", "2510_22211v1_page8_text_6", "2510_22211v1_page8_text_7", "2510_22211v1_page11_text_0", "2510_22211v1_page11_text_1", "2510_22211v1_page11_text_2", "2510_22211v1_page11_text_3", "2510_22211v1_page11_text_4", "2510_22211v1_page11_text_6", "2510_22211v1_page11_conclusion_0", "2510_22211v1_page6_text_0", "keyword::lsst", "251